                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.00/5100a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Commission to Negotiate Peace</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-08-20T14:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 20, 1919—2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2886. For <persName corresp="#p_PFL">Polk</persName>.</p>
                <p>Vice Consul Burri at headquarters of <persName corresp="#p_DGAI">General
                        Denikine</persName> in Ekaterinodar in recent report refers to officers of
                    American Military Mission in his district. Are such officers operating with
                        <persName corresp="#p_DGAI">General Denikine</persName> or elsewhere in
                    South Russia? and if so Department would be glad to know conditions which they
                    report.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
